default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;defaultOur AspirationsdefaultPlease find here a summary of our aspirations for public policy governing the relationship between the land and the people of Scotland.
default We believe that this area of public policy is in need of reform urgently if we are to achieve truly sustainable development.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe want a Scotland where……default&#xa0;
default…..default all land owners and managers understand and observe defined environmental rights and responsibilidefaultties.default We recognise and understand that the Scottish community has the right and shall decide upon the system for the economic and social division of the land between people. This division, however constituted, must be balanced by a full understanding of th
defaulte shared aspects of our dominion over land - the ecosystem cycles and services and the biodiversity that are an inseparable 
defaultfunction of the space. L
defaultegal protections must be put in place to ensure the integrity of these cycles, services and biodiversity.
default&#xa0;
default…..default the ownership or dominion over land is open and transparent.default We need public registers of land that allow us to know exactly who bears the legal duties and responsibilities for ecosystem cycles and services within any de
defaultfined space – in order that these
default duties and responsibilities
default can be enforced
default and the ecosystem services protected
default. This transparency must cover all land
default,
default and ownership 
defaultand management 
defaultby communities, ind
defaultividuals and corporate entities. It should 
defaultallow for the identification of ‘absentee’ 
defaultowners who do not live on the land owned.
default&#xa0;
default…..default all public policy for land is set out in a democratically established Land Use Strategy.default The strategy should be developed from that established in the Climate Change (Scotland) Act (2009) and should continue to be based upon the principles of environmental, social and economic sustainability. It should ensure that both communities and the eco
defaultsystem are sustained for future 
defaultgenerations. 
defaultIt should include 
defaultefficient processes to ensure the accountability of land 
defaultmanag
defaulters for their performance in delivering the strategy 
defaultand refer to
default effective regulatory system
defaults
default.
