defaulthttp://www.scotlink.org/files/publication/LINKReports/LINKReportLivingwithLand.pdf
default&#xa0;
default…..default the defaultplanning and regulatory systems for land use take account of global, national and local defaultterrestrial, freshwater and marine defaultecosystem impacts.default We need protections for ecosystem cycles, services and biodiversity which are based on the best available science 
default- including the clear designation of spaces and appropriate management responsibilities where threatened species are located, in order that biodiversity is maintained.
default&#xa0;
default……default any land taxation is designed to be economically, socially and environmentally sustadefaultinable.default It should be equitable, and underpinned by an awareness of the effect of the fiscal regime on the ecosystem and biodiversity. Alongside the promotion of economic and social development, one of the core purposes of any land taxation should be the pr
defaultotection of the ecosystem and biodiversity.
default&#xa0;
default……default any public policy subsidy for land use fully balancesdefault economic, social and defaultenvironmental concerns.default Public policy should recognise that unbalanced subsidy regimes can cause severely dangerous impacts to commun
defaultities, the ecosystem and biodiversity.
default Such public policy should also be consistent and coherent in all its many strands.
default&#xa0;
default…..default defaultopenness and public participation are central features of our governance for land use.default 
defaultWe want the methods and processes of government at 
defaultlocal and national 
defaultlevels 
defaultt
defaulto be open and properly transparent and, as a matter of course, to include genuine representatives of our communities of place and interest in all political decision-making
default&#xa0;
default….. defaulttdefaulthere is defaultrecognitiondefault thatdefault the term ‘community’ applies to both communities of place and communities of interest.default We want to see a balance
default 
defaultbetween the views of local communities and communities that seek to apply principles relating to national and global is
defaultsues of concern such as the fight against climate change or the protection of ecosystems and biodiversity.
default We believe that the community interest is best represented when communities of place and interest co-operate.
default&#xa0;
default…default.. the traditional right to roam of Sdefaultcots defaultis maintained.default The Land Reform (Scotland) Act (2003) set out in legislation for the first time the right of public access to land in Scotland
